Since you recycle the options struct, I think it is best to remove the names `allocation` and `modified_allocation`:
```
turbodbc::options options;

options.fix_unicode_allocation = false;
EXPECT_EQ(reported_size + 1, make_description(column_description, options)->element_size());

options.fix_unicode_allocation = true;
EXPECT_EQ(size_with_extra_capacity + 1, make_description(column_description, options)->element_size());
```

I think this is cleaner as:

```python
return all((self.peer_pool, self.chain, self.is_enabled))

# or
if not self.peer_pool:
    return False
elif not self.chain:
    return False
elif not self.is_enabled:
    return False
else:
    return True
```

Either would be 👍 from me.

