For readability, how about writing it like this:
```c++
DefaultInitShutdown signal_handler_uninstall_wrapper(
      SignalHandlers::InstallSignalHandler,"SendTermSignal_Unset_Test", false);
signal_handler_uninstall_wrapper.RegisterShundownHandler(SignalHandlers::UninstallSignalHandler);
```
or 
```c++
DefaultInitShutdown signal_handler_uninstall_wrapper;
signal_handler_uninstall_wrapper.RegisterInitHandler(SignalHandlers::InstallSignalHandler,"SendTermSignal_Unset_Test", false);
signal_handler_uninstall_wrapper.RegisterShundownHandler(SignalHandlers::UninstallSignalHandler);
```
And the the method `RegisterShundownHandler` can be written with `Variable parameter template` like `Init` that user can pass the `shundown func` with any parameter.
